** Privacy Policy for RootFlightAnalyst **

RootFlightAnalyst is a system designed for real-time analysis and optimization of air routes, leveraging integrations with third-party APIs and data sources. We are committed to ensuring the privacy and security of the data we collect and use. This privacy policy explains what data RootFlightAnalyst collects, how it is used, stored, and shared, in compliance with applicable data privacy regulations, including the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA).

Data Collection
RootFlightAnalyst may collect the following types of data:

Flight Data:

Real-time flight position, speed, altitude, and route information obtained through integrations with third-party APIs like Flightradar24, OpenSky Network, and FlightAware.
Historical flight data for analysis and optimization.
User Interaction Data:

Information about user interactions within the platform, including queries and commands issued to the system, for the purpose of improving functionality and performance.
Technical Information:

IP addresses, device identifiers, and usage logs may be collected to ensure system security and stability.
RootFlightAnalyst does not collect any personally identifiable information (PII) unless explicitly provided by the user (e.g., through support queries).

Use of Data
The data collected is used for the following purposes:

Real-Time Analysis and Optimization:

Data is processed to generate insights and optimize air routes based on current traffic, weather conditions, and operational constraints.
Machine Learning and Predictive Modeling:

Historical and real-time data are utilized to train machine learning models for pattern recognition, trend analysis, and performance optimization.
User Experience Enhancement:

Interaction data may be analyzed to improve system responsiveness, introduce new features, and refine the overall user experience.
Data Storage and Retention
RootFlightAnalyst stores collected data securely in encrypted databases. Data is retained for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this policy unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.

Sharing of Data
RootFlightAnalyst does not sell or rent user data. Data may be shared under the following circumstances:

Third-Party Integrations:

Data may be shared with third-party API providers to obtain additional context or insights (e.g., real-time flight status updates).
Legal Compliance:

Data may be disclosed if required by law or in response to a lawful request by public authorities.
Operational Partners:

Limited data may be shared with operational partners for the purpose of system optimization, always adhering to strict data privacy and security agreements.
Compliance with Data Regulations
RootFlightAnalyst is designed to comply with major data protection regulations, including:

GDPR:
Users within the EU have the right to access, rectify, or delete their data. They can also object to or restrict data processing and request data portability.
CCPA:
California residents have the right to know what data is collected and request the deletion of personal data.
If you wish to exercise these rights, please contact us at privacy@rootflightanalyst.com.

Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this policy periodically to reflect changes in our practices or applicable regulations. Updates will be posted on this page, and significant changes will be communicated directly to users.

Contact Information
